NAME
    whpp - WHILE pretty printer
SYNOPSIS	
    whpp sth.wh	[–all] [1] [–if] [3] [–o] [pretty-sth.wh]
DESCRIPTION
    whpp takes a program file which is syntactically correct but without formatting or a bad formatting
    and returns a well formatted program file syntactically identical.
OPTIONS	
    -all  set the default indentation to the number given in argument, default = 2
    
    -if   set the specific value for "if" indentation, default = -all argument
    
    -...  same for all other control structures (-while -for)
    
    -o    set the output file name, default = sth.whpp
    
